Package: screen-share-tab
Version: 1.1.0
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: Little Place Labs <hello@littleplacelabs.com>
Depends: ffmpeg, python3 (>= 3.9), python3-venv, curl
Recommends: xdotool, xclip, vainfo, openssl, libglib2.0-bin
Description: Stream and remote-control a Linux laptop from a tablet browser
 Stream your laptop display and external monitor to any browser on your
 local network, plus full remote control: reliable mobile typing, touchpad
 mode, audio forwarding, an app launcher with system controls, file transfer,
 and a web terminal. Hardware-accelerated encoding (NVENC/VAAPI), cursor
 highlighting, pinch-to-zoom, mDNS discovery, and auto-reconnect.
 .
 Secured by default with a PIN and self-signed TLS (https/wss).
 .
 Run 'screen-share-tab' in any terminal, then open the URL on your tablet.
